JS String Templates / Template string / Template Literals:

- we've already briefly talked what template strings do ihe previous section.

#) Interpolation:
    - Template Strings allow variables in strings.
    - Template strings provide an easy way to interpolate variables in strings.
        eg:
            let firstName = "John";
            let lastName = "Wick";
            
            document.getElementById("name").innerHTML = `full name is ${firstName} ${lastName}`;


#) Expression Substitution:
    - Template Strings allow interpolation of expressions in strings:
        eg:
            let price = 10;
            let VAT = 0.25;

            let total = `Total: ${(price * (1 + VAT)).toFixed(2)}`;
        
            document.getElementById("exp").innerHTML = total;


#) HTML Templates:

            let header = "Template strings";
            let tags = ["template strings", "js", "es6"];

            let html = `<h3> ${header} </h3> <ul>`; // <ul> tag started after header
            for(tag of tags){
                html += `<li>${tag}</li>`;
            }
            html += `</ul>` // <ul> tag closed after listing

            document.getElementById("body").innerHTML = html;